🌐 Computer Networks
1️⃣ DNS Deep Working

You already know: DNS = name → IP
Now let’s see how it actually works internally

Mental Model (Asking Directions 🗺️)

You ask:

Local person → doesn’t know
asks city office → doesn’t know
asks central office → gives answer
Actual Flow
Browser checks cache
Asks local DNS server
If not found → asks:
Root server
TLD server (.com)
Authoritative server
Gets IP → returns to browser
Why It Works

Distributed system → scalable and fast.

Memory Trick 🧠

DNS = Step-by-step search system

2️⃣ NAT Types
Types of NAT
Static NAT
Dynamic NAT
PAT (Port Address Translation)
Mental Model (Hostel Rooms 🏠)

Static → fixed room for each student
Dynamic → rooms assigned dynamically
PAT → many students share one room with different IDs

Why It Works

Efficient use of limited IP addresses.

Real Use

Home routers use PAT.

Memory Trick

Static = fixed
Dynamic = changing
PAT = many share one

3️⃣ Load Balancing
Simple Idea

Distributes traffic across multiple servers.

Mental Model (Restaurant 🍽️)

If one waiter handles all customers → slow.

Instead:

multiple waiters → faster service
Why It Works

Prevents:

server overload
slow performance
Real Example

Google uses load balancing for millions of users.

Memory Trick

Load balancing = Divide work

4️⃣ CDN (Content Delivery Network)
Simple Idea

Stores data closer to users for faster access.

Mental Model (Nearby Store 🏪)

Instead of going to main warehouse:

you buy from nearby shop
Why It Works

Reduces:

latency
load on main server
Real Example

Netflix, YouTube use CDN.

Memory Trick

CDN = Data near you

🌍 Social Networks
5️⃣ Power-Law Networks
Simple Idea

Few nodes have many connections, most have few.

Mental Model

Instagram:

few influencers → millions of followers
most users → few followers
Why It Works

Real-world networks are not evenly distributed.

Memory Trick

Few big, many small

6️⃣ Scale-Free Networks
Simple Idea

Network where some nodes become hubs.

Mental Model

Google, Facebook → hubs of internet.

Why It Works

New nodes connect to already popular nodes.

Memory Trick

Rich get richer

7️⃣ Network Resilience
Simple Idea

Ability of network to survive failures.

Mental Model

If one road closes → alternate routes exist.

Why It Matters

Internet must remain functional even if parts fail.

Memory Trick

Resilience = survive failure

8️⃣ Information Bottlenecks
Simple Idea

Points where information flow slows down.

Mental Model

Narrow road → traffic jam.

Why It Matters

Identifies weak points in network.

Memory Trick

Bottleneck = slow point

🎯 10 Most Asked Computer Network Interview Questions
1️⃣ How does DNS work?

It resolves domain names by querying multiple DNS servers step-by-step.

2️⃣ What are types of NAT?

Static, Dynamic, and PAT.

3️⃣ What is load balancing?

Distributing traffic across multiple servers.

4️⃣ What is CDN?

Network of servers storing content closer to users.

5️⃣ What is latency?

Time delay in data transmission.

6️⃣ What is a proxy server?

Acts as intermediary between client and server.

7️⃣ What is caching?

Storing frequently used data for faster access.

8️⃣ What is throughput?

Actual data transferred successfully.

9️⃣ What is QoS (Quality of Service)?

Ensures performance for critical applications.

🔟 What is jitter?

Variation in delay.

